I'm not sure why the community is attacking like rabid dogs because some relatively small time Youtuber dared to say they don't watch cutscenes in a youtube video on their own youtube account that was pretty clearly meant to get hate-clicks?

Anyway, that is to say, the person was obnoxious and used a lot of red flag language, so I am not defending them as a person at all and have never seen anything else from them so have no idea the content they create, but

I don't know if I've raged at a game in years the way I did through the fucking wine fetch quests. FFXIV has a serious issue with pacing of quests/activities just before major battles (that they STILL have) and that was the absolute worst example of it.

People's nostalgia or leisurely NG+ playthroughs are making them not realize just what a grind ARR is. Every single time you think "surely I must be nearing HW" it's, nope, still in ARR because it's twice as long as every other xpac even though half the quests are pointless.

And, yes, ARR is that bad. I literally played through it a few months ago and if not for the idea of getting to do later stuff with friends would have quit. Especially when comparing it to, for example, early SWTOR, which is actually amazing or early WoW which is super fast.

Idk I mean I think as long as skippers respect that other people don't skip and don't make a big deal about it in game/where people can't get away from them, it's not some huge deal? ARR is tedious and aggravating and it's no surprise people not super into lore start skipping.

And the complaint about YET ANOTHER snowy zone with barely anything in it was valid. The commentary on the pre-last-zone fetch quests? Also valid. Especially the one where you have to find EIGHT PEOPLE who are all over a place. That was so annoying.

Like, yeah, if they complain about stuff not making sense, it's foolish, but also considering we have to replay the dungeons in roulettes/for relics/etc long after finishing the MSQ they're part of, it is a flaw in the system they don't hold up as standalone features better.

Players without excess real world money to spend on a game they're already paying for a sub to cannot compete with people who can just buy more and more retainers.

The best way to make gil is the marketboard, the best way to make gil off the marketboard is to put up as many listings as possible. Each retainer only has 20 listing slots. The cheapest sub only comes with a single character and each character only gets 2 free retainers.
